      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form must be justified by literature precedent and sensitivity analysis for dominant physics.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact at screw-rod and screw-vertebral body block interfaces. Bilinear kinematic hardening for titanium alloy rod. Model form consistent with FDA guidance and published F1717 FEA literature. Sensitivity analysis confirmed contact stiffness and rod plasticity as dominant model form choices; both validated against experimental force-displacement curves."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to measured specimen data or certified material specifications.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V rod material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certified mill certificates for each lot. Screw geometry derived from CMM measurements of production screws (n=5 per lot). UHMWPE block modulus measured by compression testing (n=3 blocks). Input uncertainty quantified and propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (500 runs)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be production-representative and lot documentation must be available.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-released components. Lot traceability documented for screws, rods, and set screws. Specimens distributed across two independent test laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability. No deviations from production specifications noted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the full range of clinically relevant loading conditions or justify scope limitation.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under ASTM F1717 standard conditions (single static compression-bending load case, room temperature, dry). Only one load angle and one construct configuration tested. Clinical use involves a range of loading directions and in vivo temperature; however, the validation scope is limited to the standard test method. Achieved level 2 (single condition tested); required level 3 not met — identified as a credibility gap per the base COU description."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs must demonstrably correspond to measured experimental parameters within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Cross-mapping table prepared linking each model input parameter to its experimental counterpart measurement. Torque applied to set screws in test matched to model preload via calibrated torque wrench records. Block geometry in simulation matched to measured UHMWPE block dimensions. All input-to-experiment correspondences confirmed within 3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) must be below 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference must be below 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (1.42), yield force (1.61), and force at 40 mm (1.78) — all below 1.96 threshold. Percent differences: stiffness 3.8%, yield force 4.1%, force at 40 mm 6.2% — all below 10% bound. Comparison performed per ASME V&V 40 Section 7 methodology. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The relevance of the selected QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) to the clinical decision context was considered beyond the scope of the current validation activity. The assessment team noted that a formal QoI relevance mapping to patient outcomes would require clinical input outside the engineering team's remit and has been deferred to a future regulatory submission phase. No requiredLevel or achievedLevel has been established for this factor."
    },
